1
00:00:09,967 --> 00:00:11,833
<i>He'll do anything
just to make you like him.</i>

2
00:00:11,967 --> 00:00:13,333
<i>In the end,
you're the one who gets hurt.</i>

3
00:00:13,467 --> 00:00:14,633
<i> That's the kind of guy he is.</i>

4
00:00:14,767 --> 00:00:15,867
<i> What did you say to Marj?</i>

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,867
<i> Your flavor of the month.</i>

6
00:00:20,700 --> 00:00:22,633
<i>You know what this is about.
It's that woman, right?</i>

7
00:00:22,767 --> 00:00:23,833
<i> Miss Castillo?</i>

8
00:00:23,967 --> 00:00:26,000
<i>You're fighting
over the same girl?</i>

9
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:27,033
<i> To avoid trouble,</i>

10
00:00:27,167 --> 00:00:28,933
<i>I'll just stay away
from both of you.</i>

11
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:32,633
<i>Whoever you choose,
that still solves your problem.</i>

12
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:34,333
<i> You won't be alone anymore.</i>

13
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:35,433
<i>You won't have to struggle
by yourself.</i>

14
00:00:35,567 --> 00:00:37,867
<i>If there's anyone
I'd want you to marry,</i>

15
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,200
<i> it's someone like Marj.</i>

16
00:00:39,333 --> 00:00:42,233
<i>If I were you,
I wouldn't let her go.</i>

17
00:00:42,367 --> 00:00:44,300
<i>You might not find someone
like her again.</i>

18
00:00:46,267 --> 00:00:48,200
<i> Marj, I want to marry you.</i>

19
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:51,267
Paolo, are you serious?

20
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:53,867
Marriage is serious.

21
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,700
It's commitment. It's forever.

22
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:59,167
Don't joke
about something like that.

23
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:00,833
I know.

24
00:01:01,867 --> 00:01:05,300
I know it feels like
I'm rushing things.

25
00:01:05,433 --> 00:01:08,700
But if we're heading
in the same direction anyway,

26
00:01:08,867 --> 00:01:11,633
why wait?

27
00:01:15,067 --> 00:01:16,867
If you just let me,

28
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,433
I'll take care of you.

29
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:20,900
I'll protect you.

30
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:25,633
I won't let you get hurt.

31
00:01:29,133 --> 00:01:33,967
I'll take every hit for you.

32
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:36,067
Whatever comes your way.

33
00:01:37,267 --> 00:01:38,967
So you never
have to get hurt again.

34
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,267
I promise you...

35
00:01:42,433 --> 00:01:45,333
I'll make you feel safe
all the time.

36
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:52,000
I'll give you the
comfortable life you deserve.

37
00:01:52,133 --> 00:01:53,900
What about Edward?

38
00:01:54,033 --> 00:01:57,300
Marj, there's nothing he can do
if we love each other.

39
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,200
He'll move on.

40
00:02:03,667 --> 00:02:04,967
Marj,

41
00:02:05,100 --> 00:02:06,067
all this time,

42
00:02:07,667 --> 00:02:09,033
you've been the one
taking care of everyone.

43
00:02:10,467 --> 00:02:12,700
You choose to understand
everyone.

44
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:14,267
This time,

45
00:02:14,433 --> 00:02:16,600
let me do that for you.

46
00:02:17,667 --> 00:02:19,467
Let me understand you.

47
00:02:20,933 --> 00:02:23,267
Let me take care of you.

48
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:25,200
Please...

49
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:26,700
Please say yes.

50
00:02:28,233 --> 00:02:29,633
Just please say yes.

51
00:02:31,633 --> 00:02:33,033
Will you be my wife?

52
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:33,333
This is Manang Yolly and Weng.

53
00:03:33,467 --> 00:03:35,367
- Hello.
- That's Oscar.

54
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:38,467
Ma'am, you're so beautiful!

55
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:42,367
No wonder both brothers
fell for you.

56
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:43,333
Sorry? What did you say?

57
00:03:43,467 --> 00:03:46,867
Weng says
you look like a movie star.

58
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,333
Sir Paolo is so lucky.

59
00:03:48,467 --> 00:03:49,500
Yes.

60
00:03:49,633 --> 00:03:50,733
That's true.

61
00:03:50,867 --> 00:03:52,300
Thank you, Weng.

62
00:03:53,967 --> 00:03:56,267
Nice house, Pao.

63
00:03:57,300 --> 00:04:00,500
It looks like one of those
Alabang houses on our listing.

64
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:06,467
This house has been
in the family for decades.

65
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:08,833
Dad keeps renovating it, though.

66
00:04:08,967 --> 00:04:11,900
He likes updating the style.
Constantly.

67
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:15,667
Come on, let's go
see mom and dad.

68
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:19,233
Excuse us.

69
00:04:22,567 --> 00:04:24,867
Looks like Sir Paolo's
got a new life now.

70
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:29,933
This is the first time
he's brought a woman here.

71
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:31,967
But, Manang Yolly,

72
00:04:32,100 --> 00:04:36,533
doesn't Sir Edward also like
Ma'am Marj so much?

73
00:04:38,467 --> 00:04:40,167
You know how it is.

74
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:42,567
Who always wins
between the brothers?

75
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,367
<i> You're engaged?</i>

76
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:48,933
That's great!

77
00:04:49,067 --> 00:04:50,433
Congratulations!

78
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,300
<i> Congratulations?</i>

79
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:57,400
Doesn't that feel kind of fast?

80
00:04:57,533 --> 00:05:00,267
We didn't even know
they were together.

81
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:07,833
We got married
not long after meeting, too.

82
00:05:07,967 --> 00:05:10,267
They've known each
other for months.

83
00:05:13,967 --> 00:05:15,067
Mom...

84
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:17,500
you don't have anything
to worry about.

85
00:05:17,633 --> 00:05:18,467
Okay?

86
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,600
Marj is a good person.

87
00:05:20,733 --> 00:05:22,167
She's kind.

88
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:23,733
She's caring.

89
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:27,867
But times are different now.

90
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,333
You can't trust just anyone.

91
00:05:31,467 --> 00:05:34,167
We don't even know
her background.

92
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:36,133
<i> Oh, come on, Regina.</i>

93
00:05:36,267 --> 00:05:37,767
You, of all people,

94
00:05:37,900 --> 00:05:41,567
shouldn't judge a person
based on their past.

95
00:05:41,700 --> 00:05:44,467
Don't forget where we met.

96
00:05:49,467 --> 00:05:51,067
Mom...

97
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,867
don't worry.

98
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,767
I've met Marj's family.

99
00:05:56,167 --> 00:05:58,800
Her background isn't perfect,

100
00:05:58,933 --> 00:06:00,267
but I've known her enough...

101
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:04,700
to say I'm making
the right choice.

102
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:08,333
That's okay, son. That's okay.

103
00:06:09,233 --> 00:06:11,400
Have you told your brother?

104
00:06:11,533 --> 00:06:15,100
I hope you're considering
Edward's feelings.

105
00:06:15,233 --> 00:06:17,900
Edward isn't a child anymore
to mope.

106
00:06:18,033 --> 00:06:20,967
He should man up
and just deal with it.

107
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:33,433
<i> What if your mom's right?</i>

108
00:06:33,567 --> 00:06:36,733
What if this engagement
is too fast?

109
00:06:37,867 --> 00:06:38,833
It is fast.

110
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:42,367
But...

111
00:06:42,533 --> 00:06:43,867
don't worry.

112
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,600
I've got this.

113
00:06:45,733 --> 00:06:47,900
I mean, look at my parents.

114
00:06:48,033 --> 00:06:52,000
They got engaged in ten days
and are still together now.

115
00:06:52,133 --> 00:06:55,633
Your mom doesn't seem happy
about us.

116
00:06:55,767 --> 00:06:58,367
Don't mind what she said.

117
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:03,100
Edward's always been
her favorite.

118
00:07:03,233 --> 00:07:05,100
That's why I wasn't surprised.

119
00:07:07,033 --> 00:07:09,833
She's just worried
about my brother.

120
00:07:12,533 --> 00:07:13,967
Don't think about it, okay?

121
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:18,833
Once she sees
how serious we are,

122
00:07:18,967 --> 00:07:21,933
she'll give us her blessing.
Okay?

123
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:35,833
So you won't feel sad anymore...

124
00:07:35,967 --> 00:07:37,867
I have a surprise.

125
00:07:43,133 --> 00:07:44,633
Pao, it's beautiful.

126
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:51,267
I got the best engagement ring,

127
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:53,500
so everyone knows...

128
00:07:53,633 --> 00:07:54,967
you're taken.

129
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:00,900
That's it?

130
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:03,200
That's all I can get?

131
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:06,800
Manang Yolly?

132
00:08:06,933 --> 00:08:08,567
- Sir Edward?
- Sir.

133
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:12,700
Sir, don't you have
a client meeting today?

134
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:17,400
Yeah. We thought
you'd be home later, Sir.

135
00:08:17,533 --> 00:08:19,633
It ended early.

136
00:08:19,767 --> 00:08:20,767
Where's everybody?

137
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:31,133
Pao, what are you doing?

138
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,733
Why?

139
00:08:33,867 --> 00:08:35,600
We're inside the house.

140
00:08:35,733 --> 00:08:39,433
- Someone might see us.
- We're getting married anyway.

141
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:49,333
Sir, your parents
are just over there.

142
00:08:49,467 --> 00:08:51,667
Why don't you rest in your room?

143
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:54,800
I'll bring you snacks later.

144
00:08:54,967 --> 00:08:56,500
Go on.

145
00:08:56,633 --> 00:08:59,767
Why do you look nervous?

146
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:01,633
Is there a problem?

147
00:09:01,767 --> 00:09:03,700
No, Sir. None.

148
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,067
Oh God.

149
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,667
Here we go again.

150
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:24,367
Let's just do this
when we're alone.

151
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:25,933
When we're alone,

152
00:09:26,067 --> 00:09:28,033
we'll do more than that.

153
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,500
You're so silly.

154
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:33,933
Have some respect
for the woman, Paolo.

155
00:09:36,667 --> 00:09:39,300
People might think...

156
00:09:39,433 --> 00:09:42,133
Marj is easy to get,
just like your other girls.

157
00:09:43,933 --> 00:09:45,800
Edward, it's okay.

158
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:48,100
We just got carried away.

159
00:09:48,233 --> 00:09:49,567
Relax, Bro.

160
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:50,967
We're just happy.

161
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:53,433
We shared the good news
with mom and dad.

162
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:56,833
What good news?

163
00:10:05,033 --> 00:10:06,467
So you've made your decision.

164
00:10:08,067 --> 00:10:09,500
Edward, I'm sorry.

165
00:10:10,967 --> 00:10:12,700
Congrats.

166
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:13,667
Edward!

167
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:15,667
Marj, let him be.

168
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:19,267
No, Pao. I hurt him.

169
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:21,233
I need to talk to him.

170
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:37,200
Edward!

171
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:40,133
Edward, wait. Just a second.
Talk to me.

172
00:10:40,267 --> 00:10:41,567
What?

173
00:10:41,700 --> 00:10:42,667
Just a second.

174
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:46,500
Paolo, what were you thinking?

175
00:10:46,633 --> 00:10:48,167
You could've had
any other woman.

176
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:52,333
Why go after
the woman Edward likes?

177
00:10:52,467 --> 00:10:54,667
Why is Edward
always the priority?

178
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:56,533
You always take his side.

179
00:10:56,667 --> 00:10:58,100
I'm your son, too.

180
00:10:59,300 --> 00:11:02,467
Paolo, it's not favoritism,

181
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,567
but...

182
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:06,067
Edward isn't like you.

183
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:08,333
Everyone loves you.

184
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:12,633
He only has me.

185
00:11:12,767 --> 00:11:17,067
And now you're taking
the woman he loves.

186
00:11:18,067 --> 00:11:20,433
I never meant to hurt you.

187
00:11:21,767 --> 00:11:22,800
If you don't want me
to get hurt,

188
00:11:22,933 --> 00:11:24,300
you can still change your mind.

189
00:11:25,233 --> 00:11:27,033
You still have time to back out.

190
00:11:27,167 --> 00:11:29,433
I didn't take anything from him.

191
00:11:29,567 --> 00:11:31,800
Marj was never his
to begin with.

192
00:11:31,933 --> 00:11:34,567
But you knew he liked her first.

193
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:36,833
Yes. I'm aware of that.

194
00:11:36,967 --> 00:11:38,833
But I acted. He didn't.

195
00:11:38,967 --> 00:11:41,133
And Marj chose me.

196
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:43,967
I warned you about Paolo.
You didn't listen.

197
00:11:45,533 --> 00:11:47,633
If you marry him,

198
00:11:47,767 --> 00:11:49,467
you'll be miserable.

199
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:53,300
Can't you see this woman
is tearing our family apart?

200
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:57,100
Because of this,
I will never accept her.

201
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:01,667
I'm not cursing you.

202
00:12:03,067 --> 00:12:04,800
But you will get hurt.

203
00:12:04,933 --> 00:12:07,533
And don't say
I didn't warn you.

204
00:12:07,667 --> 00:12:09,367
Then my decision is final.

205
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,200
Marj and I are getting married.

206
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:14,500
And there's nothing you
or Edward can do to stop it.

207
00:12:19,100 --> 00:12:20,100
Edward.

208
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:23,500
Edward.

209
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,067
Do you still feel guilty
about Edward?

210
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:53,000
Yeah.

211
00:12:53,133 --> 00:12:55,533
Paolo, this is my fault.

212
00:12:55,667 --> 00:12:57,900
I should've talked to him first

213
00:12:58,033 --> 00:12:59,300
before I said yes
to your proposal.

214
00:12:59,433 --> 00:13:01,167
I should've prepared him.

215
00:13:01,300 --> 00:13:03,100
I feel the same.

216
00:13:03,233 --> 00:13:05,900
I feel guilty, too.

217
00:13:06,033 --> 00:13:08,033
I should've told him
ahead of time

218
00:13:08,167 --> 00:13:10,267
that I was going to propose
to you.

219
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:11,800
But...

220
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:15,100
what's done is done.

221
00:13:15,233 --> 00:13:18,733
We can't just throw away
our plans because of him.

222
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:24,033
Love...

223
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:29,167
Don't think about Edward
too much, okay?

224
00:13:31,033 --> 00:13:32,867
He's probably...

225
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,700
just emotional and angry
right now.

226
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,633
What he said
won't really happen, right?

227
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:45,100
Of course not.

228
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:48,567
Once we're married,

229
00:13:48,700 --> 00:13:51,767
I'll make you the happiest woman
in the world.

230
00:13:56,633 --> 00:13:58,367
Okay.

231
00:13:58,500 --> 00:14:00,933
When Edward's calmed down,

232
00:14:01,067 --> 00:14:03,433
I'll talk to him.

233
00:14:03,567 --> 00:14:05,833
But for now,

234
00:14:05,967 --> 00:14:08,167
can you not engage with him?

235
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:13,233
I don't want him
affecting our plans.

236
00:14:14,633 --> 00:14:17,633
And if you really matter to him,

237
00:14:17,767 --> 00:14:19,967
shouldn't he just be happy
for you?

238
00:14:28,867 --> 00:14:31,600
<i>Hey, Jobert, you'll be living
here soon, okay?</i>

239
00:14:31,733 --> 00:14:35,167
<i>Look how big this place is.
You and Pong can play here.</i>

240
00:14:36,767 --> 00:14:40,000
Pong, Paolo's house is huge!

241
00:14:40,133 --> 00:14:41,733
You'll get lost in there, Pong.

242
00:14:43,433 --> 00:14:44,400
Marj!

243
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:49,733
Paolo's house is so big!

244
00:14:49,867 --> 00:14:51,500
- Yeah.
- I think Pong and I

245
00:14:51,633 --> 00:14:53,733
will get lost there.

246
00:14:53,867 --> 00:14:55,600
It's like a palace, right?

247
00:15:01,900 --> 00:15:05,300
<i>There. There they are.
You'll be with them here, okay?</i>

248
00:15:06,300 --> 00:15:09,433
<i>I'll come closer
so you can see them better.</i>

249
00:15:13,133 --> 00:15:16,267
That woman in the painting
is scary.

250
00:15:18,700 --> 00:15:20,567
That's Paolo's mother.

251
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:22,533
She's kind too, just like him.

252
00:15:23,967 --> 00:15:28,467
She doesn't look kind.
She looks like a witch.

253
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:30,400
A pretty witch.

254
00:15:33,133 --> 00:15:38,067
Jobert, we'll live there
once I marry Paolo.

255
00:15:39,667 --> 00:15:40,967
Why?

256
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,633
Because...

257
00:15:44,767 --> 00:15:47,000
our life will be better.

258
00:15:48,433 --> 00:15:51,067
That's why I'm marrying him.

259
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,433
Not just because I love him.

260
00:15:53,567 --> 00:15:56,167
I'm also doing this for you.

261
00:15:56,300 --> 00:15:58,100
So we won't struggle anymore.

262
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:06,267
What if people there are mean?

263
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:11,200
What if Paolo's mom
is mean?

264
00:16:11,367 --> 00:16:13,700
And the people there, too?

265
00:16:15,833 --> 00:16:18,533
<i>I warned you about Paolo,
but you wouldn't listen.</i>

266
00:16:18,667 --> 00:16:19,833
<i> You're engaged?</i>

267
00:16:19,967 --> 00:16:21,467
<i> That's great!</i>

268
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,333
<i> Doesn't it seem too fast?</i>

269
00:16:23,467 --> 00:16:25,633
<i>We didn't even know
they were together.</i>

270
00:16:25,767 --> 00:16:29,167
<i>If you go through with this
marriage, you'll be miserable.</i>

271
00:16:31,733 --> 00:16:33,000
Marj...

272
00:16:35,067 --> 00:16:37,600
Don't worry.

273
00:16:37,733 --> 00:16:39,967
I will protect you.

274
00:16:43,567 --> 00:16:46,200
I love you.

275
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:50,867
I love you, too.

276
00:17:04,933 --> 00:17:06,600
Anyway, Edward.

277
00:17:06,733 --> 00:17:11,433
I'm glad we're partnering
with Torrecampo Realty.

278
00:17:11,567 --> 00:17:14,667
It'll really help sell
our business properties.

279
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:17,900
As I said, we'll make sure your
properties are sold on time.

280
00:17:18,067 --> 00:17:21,000
By the way, how's Paolo?

281
00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:23,400
I was kind of expecting him
to handle this,

282
00:17:23,533 --> 00:17:26,667
since he was the first one
I spoke to.

283
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,600
Is he unavailable?

284
00:17:28,733 --> 00:17:32,133
I heard he's the best
in your company.

285
00:17:32,267 --> 00:17:34,500
I'm just as capable as Paolo.

286
00:17:34,633 --> 00:17:35,933
Actually, more capable.

287
00:17:36,067 --> 00:17:38,800
Because I'm serious, loyal,
and I do my job right.

288
00:17:38,933 --> 00:17:40,367
I don't deceive people.

289
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:41,600
But Paolo?

290
00:17:41,733 --> 00:17:44,033
He's the worst person
you could choose over me.

291
00:17:44,167 --> 00:17:45,967
He's a traitor. He steals
what isn't his. He's selfish.

292
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,233
That's who Paolo is.

293
00:17:49,367 --> 00:17:50,600
He looks nice at first,

294
00:17:50,733 --> 00:17:53,033
but once he gets what he wants,
he drops you.

295
00:17:54,067 --> 00:17:55,133
He's...

296
00:17:55,267 --> 00:17:56,500
two-faced.

297
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:00,600
Wait,

298
00:18:00,733 --> 00:18:01,567
he's your brother.

299
00:18:01,700 --> 00:18:03,833
But it sounds like
you're trashing him.

300
00:18:03,967 --> 00:18:06,167
That's just how he is.

301
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:09,767
If you buy property from Paolo,
that's it. You're done.

302
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:13,767
He leaves you the moment
he gets what he wants.

303
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:16,933
In the end,
you're the one who suffers.

304
00:18:17,067 --> 00:18:18,900
No after-sales service.

305
00:18:26,233 --> 00:18:27,067
Hey.

306
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:29,500
Something smells good.
Is that Adobo?

307
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:34,933
Mom!

308
00:18:36,833 --> 00:18:38,467
- Mom!
- How are you?

309
00:18:44,567 --> 00:18:47,933
You're home again, Mom.

310
00:18:48,067 --> 00:18:50,467
You'll be with me again.

311
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:53,900
It's not that easy, sweetheart.

312
00:18:54,033 --> 00:18:56,900
But I'll visit you often.

313
00:18:57,067 --> 00:18:59,767
I cooked your favorite adobo.

314
00:19:01,267 --> 00:19:02,600
Mom...

315
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:15,400
Mom, are you sure you
don't want to take a taxi?

316
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,900
Oh, it's fine.

317
00:19:19,033 --> 00:19:20,733
I can get a ride nearby anyway.

318
00:19:20,867 --> 00:19:23,200
How's dad been treating you?

319
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:26,900
It's okay so far.

320
00:19:27,033 --> 00:19:28,833
He hasn't disrespected me
lately.

321
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:31,400
Oh, dear...

322
00:19:31,533 --> 00:19:33,400
I'm sorry, my child.

323
00:19:33,533 --> 00:19:37,033
I know I complicated
our lives.

324
00:19:37,167 --> 00:19:40,433
And I know
you've been struggling.

325
00:19:42,967 --> 00:19:44,267
That's true.

326
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:48,433
But I've found someone to face
everything with me, Mom.

327
00:19:50,933 --> 00:19:52,000
What?

328
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:56,067
I'm getting married to Paolo.

329
00:19:57,933 --> 00:19:59,567
Paolo?

330
00:19:59,700 --> 00:20:02,433
Sir Paolo Torrecampo?

331
00:20:05,633 --> 00:20:06,800
Oh, sweetie.

332
00:20:06,933 --> 00:20:10,400
Your dream finally came true,
someone's committing to you,

333
00:20:10,533 --> 00:20:13,333
just like you always wanted.

334
00:20:15,733 --> 00:20:18,300
This is important, sweetheart.

335
00:20:18,433 --> 00:20:20,667
We need to prepare for it.

336
00:20:22,567 --> 00:20:26,167
What if I talk to your father?

337
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:28,067
So he can walk you down
the aisle?

338
00:20:30,333 --> 00:20:31,733
Mom, no.

339
00:20:33,233 --> 00:20:35,567
I don't want to invite dad.

340
00:20:37,967 --> 00:20:39,767
It's okay. I'm fine.

341
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:43,100
And please don't bring him
as a guest.

342
00:20:52,967 --> 00:20:54,400
Hey, make sure you come

343
00:20:54,533 --> 00:20:57,133
to Sir Paolo and Marj's
engagement party, okay?

344
00:20:57,267 --> 00:20:58,233
Are you now official?

345
00:20:58,367 --> 00:20:59,133
Yeah.

346
00:20:59,267 --> 00:21:02,133
Oh my God, congrats!

347
00:21:02,267 --> 00:21:04,167
Wow, your observation skills
are terrible.

348
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:05,367
They've been together forever.

349
00:21:05,500 --> 00:21:06,233
Wait, you two? Since when?

350
00:21:06,367 --> 00:21:08,267
You're totally
in your own world.

351
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,333
See you, okay?

352
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:11,367
- See you at the wedding.
- Thank you, Marj.

353
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:13,567
Thank you.

354
00:21:13,700 --> 00:21:14,833
They have no idea.

355
00:21:14,967 --> 00:21:16,167
They're hilarious.

356
00:21:16,300 --> 00:21:17,267
Girl.

357
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:19,233
Are the brothers okay now?

358
00:21:20,333 --> 00:21:22,167
How could you do this?

359
00:21:22,300 --> 00:21:23,567
You ruined the relationship

360
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:27,067
we spent years building
with Mr. Chen!

361
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,167
I'm sorry, Dad.

362
00:21:33,167 --> 00:21:36,300
If you're jealous of your
brother because of Marj,

363
00:21:36,433 --> 00:21:39,033
don't drag the business into it.

364
00:21:39,167 --> 00:21:41,300
I worked my whole life
to build this,

365
00:21:41,433 --> 00:21:44,167
and you're destroying it
because of your stupidity.

366
00:21:49,633 --> 00:21:51,000
<i> That's enough, Dad!</i>

367
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:54,867
Do you think I've contributed
nothing to this company?

368
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,233
I've done so much!
You just never notice!

369
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:00,133
What did you say?

370
00:22:00,267 --> 00:22:02,933
Do I need to mess up
just to get your attention?

371
00:22:04,767 --> 00:22:08,400
All you ever do is take
all your anger out on me!

372
00:22:10,033 --> 00:22:13,133
Nothing I do is ever right
in your eyes!

373
00:22:13,267 --> 00:22:16,367
You treat me like
I'm not even your real son!

374
00:22:21,733 --> 00:22:23,500
You still have the nerve
to talk back.

375
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:27,500
You're shameless.

376
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:28,600
You're fired!

377
00:22:28,733 --> 00:22:29,867
No!

378
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,667
You can't fire me!

379
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:33,600
I'm a Torrecampo!

380
00:22:33,733 --> 00:22:37,467
I'm your boss.
And I say you're fired!

381
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:39,833
What? Get out!

382
00:22:39,967 --> 00:22:40,867
Get out!

383
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:41,967
Get out!

384
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:45,333
Leave our house, too!

385
00:22:45,467 --> 00:22:49,167
I don't want to see your face
when I come home.

386
00:22:49,333 --> 00:22:51,800
Get out! Out!

387
00:22:51,933 --> 00:22:53,733
I said, out!

388
00:22:53,867 --> 00:22:55,167
Out!

389
00:23:36,300 --> 00:23:37,500
Edward?

390
00:23:37,633 --> 00:23:38,867
Are you okay?

391
00:23:40,133 --> 00:23:41,067
Please...

392
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,633
stop.

393
00:23:47,733 --> 00:23:50,100
You know,
I can't even blame you...

394
00:23:50,233 --> 00:23:51,967
for not liking me.

395
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:55,867
My own father doesn't want me.

396
00:23:57,533 --> 00:24:01,033
Edward, don't say that.

397
00:24:01,167 --> 00:24:02,400
But honestly,

398
00:24:02,533 --> 00:24:04,233
this might actually...

399
00:24:04,367 --> 00:24:06,533
be good for me.

400
00:24:06,667 --> 00:24:08,833
Being rejected by my dad...

401
00:24:08,967 --> 00:24:13,033
gives me time to move on
from you. To start over.

402
00:24:14,167 --> 00:24:17,200
To go somewhere where
there's no one...

403
00:24:17,333 --> 00:24:19,100
who doesn't want me out.

404
00:24:24,833 --> 00:24:26,067
Edward.

405
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:28,200
Edward, please.

406
00:24:40,133 --> 00:24:41,900
Edward, my son,
please don't leave.

407
00:24:42,033 --> 00:24:43,467
I'm sure
your father was just shocked.

408
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:44,967
That's why he said those things.
Please.

409
00:24:45,100 --> 00:24:47,667
No, Mom. He was very clear.

410
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:49,033
He wants me out of this house.

411
00:24:49,167 --> 00:24:51,800
No. Don't worry.
I'll talk to him.

412
00:24:51,933 --> 00:24:53,300
I'm sure he'll change his mind.

413
00:24:53,433 --> 00:24:54,800
No, Mom. Enough.

414
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,000
We both know we don't have
a voice in this house.

415
00:24:59,233 --> 00:25:01,033
You'll just waste
all your efforts. Your energy.

416
00:25:02,167 --> 00:25:03,200
What's the point?

417
00:25:07,133 --> 00:25:09,900
This is all
Marj Castillo's fault.

418
00:25:10,033 --> 00:25:11,733
She's the one
tearing this family apart.

419
00:25:11,867 --> 00:25:13,067
No, no, no, no, Mom.

420
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:14,500
Listen to me.

421
00:25:16,033 --> 00:25:19,033
Don't be angry at Marj.
Don't blame her.

422
00:25:19,167 --> 00:25:20,900
She's just a victim
of circumstance.

423
00:25:22,933 --> 00:25:24,000
Mom...

424
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:27,900
please be nice to her.

425
00:25:28,033 --> 00:25:29,267
For me.

426
00:25:30,333 --> 00:25:32,133
Even if she didn't choose me,
I still love her.

427
00:25:32,267 --> 00:25:33,733
I still...

428
00:25:33,867 --> 00:25:35,233
I still care about her.

429
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:38,700
Don't be mad at her anymore.

430
00:25:38,833 --> 00:25:40,233
Promise me, okay?

431
00:25:44,067 --> 00:25:45,033
Okay.

432
00:25:46,967 --> 00:25:48,533
Fine.

433
00:25:48,667 --> 00:25:49,667
Thank you, Mom.

434
00:25:50,900 --> 00:25:52,233
I'll call you.

435
00:26:01,767 --> 00:26:03,133
Ma'am, your coffee.

436
00:26:05,900 --> 00:26:07,933
I've been asking for that!
Why only now?

437
00:26:09,767 --> 00:26:11,867
- Clean that up!
- Yes, Ma'am.

438
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,233
Stupid!

439
00:26:20,967 --> 00:26:22,067
Oh, Marj.

440
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:23,167
Let me show you
a little preview.

441
00:26:23,300 --> 00:26:25,533
- Marj is here.
- Good evening.

442
00:26:25,667 --> 00:26:27,267
I hope this is the start

443
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:29,033
of a good relationship
between us.

444
00:26:29,167 --> 00:26:31,967
It seems that she's just
pretending to be nice.

445
00:26:32,100 --> 00:26:34,533
Marj Castillo is marrying
your brother?

446
00:26:34,667 --> 00:26:36,500
Why? Do you know her?

447
00:26:36,633 --> 00:26:39,500
Oh my gosh,
I'm more than thrilled.

448
00:26:39,633 --> 00:26:40,700
It feels like I'm being stabbed.

449
00:26:40,833 --> 00:26:43,033
Because you hurt my family.

450
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:45,900
So Marj
is becoming a Torrecampo now.

451
00:26:46,033 --> 00:26:47,467
Welcome home, Marj.

452
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:52,500
Even if you marry Paolo,
I will never accept you.

453
00:26:52,633 --> 00:26:54,267
I know that no matter
what we do,

454
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:57,100
they'll never accept
our relationship.

455
00:26:57,233 --> 00:26:58,933
So what are you saying now?

456
00:26:59,067 --> 00:27:01,833
Maybe we shouldn't get married.
